<TITLE> 6-grade earthquake rocks parts of country </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 4 (bdnews24.com)--An earthquake measuring 6 on Richter scale rocked Dhaka, Sylhet and Chittagong Hill Tracts in the wee hours of Friday, a Met Office official said. The assistant meteorologist at Bangladesh Meteorological Department, Bazlur Rashid, told bdnews24.com said the epicenter of the tremor was on the Myanmar-India border, 424 kilometers away from the BMD Seismic Centre in Dhaka. No damages were reported as the quake took place deep in the ground, he said. Rashid also said no tsunami alert was were issued in the aftermath of the quake. Earlier on Aug 31, a tremor measuring 5.3 was felt in Sylhet and its surroundings. Around 250,000 buildings in the three major cities of BangladeshDhaka, Chittagong and Sylhetare extremely vulnerable to earthquakes, according to a recent survey. Some 142,000 among 180,000 buildings in Chittagong; 24,000 out of 52,000 in Sylhet; and 78,000 out of 326,000 buildings in Dhaka were detected as risky according to A S M Maksud Kamal, national adviser on tsunami, cyclone and earthquake risk of the Comprehensive Disaster Management Programme (CDMP). bd
